## Query 10: Job Level Satisfaction Analysis

Identifies which job levels are at risk and their average characteristics.

```sql
SELECT 
  JobLevel,
  COUNT(*) as employee_count,
  ROUND(AVG(JobSatisfaction), 2) as avg_satisfaction,
  ROUND(AVG(Age), 1) as avg_age,
  ROUND(AVG(Experience), 1) as avg_experience
FROM employeesurvey.employees
GROUP BY JobLevel
ORDER BY 
  CASE JobLevel
    WHEN 'Intern/Fresher' THEN 1
    WHEN 'Junior' THEN 2
    WHEN 'Mid' THEN 3
    WHEN 'Lead' THEN 4
    WHEN 'Senior' THEN 5
  END;
```

**Purpose:** Identify vulnerable job levels. Result: 41 Senior leaders at-risk (4.68% of Senior cohort—critical retention concern).

---

## Query 11: Commute Impact on Satisfaction

Examines if commute mode and distance affect satisfaction and WLB.

```sql
SELECT 
  CommuteMode,
  COUNT(*) as employee_count,
  ROUND(AVG(CommuteDistance), 2) as avg_distance_km,
  ROUND(AVG(JobSatisfaction), 2) as avg_satisfaction,
  ROUND(AVG(WLB), 2) as avg_wlb
FROM employeesurvey.employees
GROUP BY CommuteMode
ORDER BY avg_satisfaction DESC;
```

**Purpose:** Secondary analysis on commute impact. Helps identify if remote/flexible options could improve satisfaction.

---

## Query 12: Training Investment Analysis

Examines if training hours correlate with retention potential and satisfaction.

```sql
SELECT 
  JobLevel,
  COUNT(*) as employee_count,
  ROUND(AVG(TrainingHoursPerYear), 2) as avg_training_hours,
  MIN(TrainingHoursPerYear) as min_training,
  MAX(TrainingHoursPerYear) as max_training,
  ROUND(AVG(JobSatisfaction), 2) as avg_satisfaction
FROM employeesurvey.employees
GROUP BY JobLevel
ORDER BY 
  CASE JobLevel
    WHEN 'Intern/Fresher' THEN 1
    WHEN 'Junior' THEN 2
    WHEN 'Mid' THEN 3
    WHEN 'Lead' THEN 4
    WHEN 'Senior' THEN 5
  END;
```

**Purpose:** Measure training investment equity and correlation with satisfaction. Result: Inconsistent investment across levels. Junior staff receive 6% fewer training hours than Senior roles.

